        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 3:01AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 301 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Chapman, or 12 miles northeast of Grand Island, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Chapman around 305 AM CDT.
Marquette around 315 AM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
